added to recovery hopes. "Like the chip industry as a whole, ASML sees signs of recovery riddled with inconsistencies," ASML Chief Executive Doug Dunn said. Headlines.Headline: Circuit City Sees Net Jump 15%

PARAGRAPH.#text:
Consumer electronics retailer
 Circuit
City Group reported a 15% increase in second-quarter earnings, boosted by
strong demand for satellite-television services, big-screen TVs and
wireless phones.

Headlines.Headline: Circuit City Unit To Match Estimates

PARAGRAPH.#text:
Circuit City Stores
 said it expects
quarterly earnings at its consumer-electronics unit to rise about 15%, in
line with analysts' estimates.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Circuit City Unit To Match Estimates
Headlines.Provider: The Wall Street Journal Interactive Edition

PARAGRAPH.#text:

said earnings will be flat ... McClatchy
 said earnings will top expectations by 10% ...
Circuit City
 reported a small jump in net income.

Headlines.Headline: Superstores Jack Up Car Prices

PARAGRAPH.#text:
Large used-car
chains
 that were expected to push down prices have
done just the opposite, according to a new survey of six Southeastern
markets.

Headlines.Author: Susan Pulliam
Headlines.Headline:
Reviews Are Weak
For Two Big IPOs

PARAGRAPH.#text:
The first
 two big-name initial public
offerings of 1997 had their Wall Street premiere Tuesday: CarMax Group, a
national used-car seller, and Vail Resorts, a ski-resort operator. But
investors' reviews of both deals were weak.
